This paper deals with the problem of multi-broadcast in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also presents algorithms that are scalable with respect to the diameter of the network and the polylogarithm of the network size, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of the SINR model, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT), and the paper presents deterministic algorithms, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
